Description: Women of Coffee is a California C Corporation that was incorporated in December 2013 by Karen Cebreros.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Women of Coffee is a California C Corporation that was incorporated in December 2013 by Karen Cebreros, a serial entrepreneur focused on developing social businesses. Cebreros, CEO of Women of Coffee, is a pioneer in the sustainability efforts in the coffee industry and was the leader in visioning, developing and implementing the introduction of organic green coffee bean trading in North America. Women of Coffee provides products and services that empower corporations, employees and industries to measure, track and ultimately increase activities that improve human engagement, environmental impact and profitability.   The development of Corporate Cares was strongly driven by Cerebros’s vision: “They imagine unleashing the power of and potential of every employee to revitalize their community.”  With an already established, vertically integrated market in the coffee and beverage industry, Women of Coffee is expanding its reach to the larger corporate market.   Women of Coffee is seeking a total of up to US $350,000 to market and sell Corporate Cares.  The company is selling 700,000 shares at $.50/share which represents 35% of the company.  There is a minimum investment of $5,000.  Women of Coffee intends to buy back its equity from their investors in Year 5 based on a third-party valuation.  The investor can also choose to retain its equity until Exit Strategy is executed in later years. Exit Strategy will depend on certain market conditions. Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The Granary is an upbeat, welcoming, quilt shop located at the corner of South Mary Avenue and West Fremont Avenue in Sunnyvale, California. Why is it called The Granary, you ask? Well in the fabled mists of the local quilt world, the first Granary quilt shop began in San Juan Bautista, California, about 40 years ago, and the owner was from a ranching family, and had a granary.....Fast forward about four decades and several owners, and we have The Granary Quilt Shop of today.  After 17+ years under the care of the prior owner, as of December 2017 the shop is under the care of new owner, Audrey Vallen. The Granary has a wide array of fabulous fabric to appeal to a range of quilters and sewists, whether you find yourself on the traditional or modern end of the spectrum. The shop is filled to the brim with Batiks, grunge, nostalgic 1930s, 19th century repros, novelties, and modern designers from FreeSpirit and Art Gallery.  We also have an extensive color wall to find the perfect supporting fabrics to go with that special fabric that makes your heart go pitter pat!  Allow our experienced staff to help you with your design choices, if you like. We are happy to talk quilting, and recommend a class or project, if you are new to this hobby (ahem -obsession!) Discover patterns, books galore, quilting tools and notions. We have lots of samples displayed to inspire you.  We also carry Valdani pearl cotton and wool, and English paper piecing supplies, for those who enjoy hand work. We hope to delight you with our fabric, inspire you with classes, and provide plenty of quilting comradery in the new year!

Description: LMI-Vet: LMI-Vet is the veterinary subsidiary of Lifeblood Medical, Inc.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: LMI-Vet is the veterinary subsidiary of Lifeblood Medical, Inc. LMI-Vet is positioned to enter the stable, growing, multi-billion dollar veterinary market with a new, break-through critical care product, which satisfies a major market gap for companion animals. Like human medicine, the need for a non-toxic Fluid Replacement for dehydration and severe bleeding is considered the holy grail for emergency medicine. Previously, Oxyglobin®, a bovine hemoglobin product, confirmed the need for a veterinary blood substitute, which product is no longer available in the US. Currently, US veterinarians must resort to blood products to satisfy their fluid replacement needs, which have limited shelf life, supply issues, cross-matching requirements, and other market factors, which maintain a need for Dexsome 510 which enhances tissue oxygenation, electrolyte balance,and supplies nutrients. Certain hetastarch products are under scrutiny in the US and banned in Europe, which may create additional demand for dextran based IV solutions. DEXSOME 510 is a new, dextran-based crystalloid, colloid intravenous solution which proposes to become the gold standard for replacement fluids. LMI-Vet Solution will be sold as a replacement fluid, without drug claims, applied to the product. The current competition is threefold, being existing replacement fluids, blood products (whole blood, packed red cells), and Oxyglobin®, which has a controlled  reintroduction in Europe, with a pending re-introduction into the US market by 2015. The key differentiators for LMI-Vet Solution will be easier handling, universal use, reduced cost, and superior safety profile. The differentiating features of LMI-Vet will be established using emerging marketing tactics.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Jasmere also turns typical 'supply and demand' economics on its ear, in that more demand for jasmere products actually *lowers* the price everyone pays.  Thanks to specially negotiated deals with their featured merchants, jasmere lowers the price over the course of the day, as more people buy. No credit cards are charged until the feature ends, and everyone pays the same low price. Jasmere was launched in December 2009.
